Let's enhance your authentication system to properly store and retrieve user data from Firestore. The good news is that your `AuthViewModel` already has most of the functionality in place, but we need to make sure the real-time updates work correctly.

## Current Implementation

Looking at your code, I can see you're already:

1. Creating user documents in Firestore when users sign up
2. Using the user's UID as the document ID (which is perfect)
3. Storing `UserData` objects with user information

## Enhancements Needed

Let's make these improvements:

1. Use a Firestore listener for real-time updates
2. Ensure profile updates are immediately reflected in the UI
3. Add proper error handling and loading states
4. Create a separate user management method

Here are the changes:

## 1. Update AuthViewModel with Real-Time Listener

```kotlin:app/src/main/java/android/saswat/viewModel/Auth View Model.kt
// Add this field to track the Firestore listener
private var userListener: ListenerRegistration? = null

// Update the fetchUserData method to use a listener instead of one-time get()
fun fetchUserData() {
 val currentUser = auth.currentUser ?: return

 // Cancel any existing listener
 userListener?.remove()

 // Set up a real-time listener for the user document
 userListener = firestore.collection("users").document(currentUser.uid)
 .addSnapshotListener { snapshot, error ->
 if (error != null) {
 Log.e("AuthViewModel", "Error listening for user data changes", error)
 return@addSnapshotListener
 }

 if (snapshot != null && snapshot.exists()) {
 val userData = snapshot.toObject(UserData::class.java)
 _userData.value = userData?.copy(userId = currentUser.uid)
 } else {
 Log.d("AuthViewModel", "User document does not exist")
 _userData.value = null
 }
 }
}

// Make sure to clean up the listener in onCleared
override fun onCleared() {
 super.onCleared()
 userListener?.remove()
}

// Update signOut to also remove the listener
fun signOut() {
 userListener?.remove()
 auth.signOut()
 _authState.value = AuthState.Initial
 _userData.value = null
 _updateState.value = UpdateState.Idle
}
