These changes will create a complete Firestore database integration where:

1. User data is stored under the user's UID in a "users" collection
2. Profile updates are immediately reflected in the UI thanks to the real-time listener
3. Users can view and edit their profile information
4. The system has proper error handling and success feedback

With this implementation, any changes made to user data will be immediately stored in Firestore and reflected in your app's UI. The real-time listener keeps everything synchronized without requiring manual refreshes."},{"role":"user","content":"<additional_data>
