The three options give you different ways to position the logo at the top while adjusting the size and position of the background image. The first version puts the background in the middle as a flexible element that takes up any available space between the top and bottom elements. The second version makes the background a fixed size card with a shadow. The third version places the background at the bottom taking up 40% of screen height.

All three layouts follow the pattern of:
1. Logo and app name at the top
2. Background image as a design element (but not taking over the entire screen)
